** The Difficult Art of Self-Compassion (https://www.brainpickings.org/201=
6/09/05/school-of-life-self-compassion/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNI=
QID])
------------------------------------------------------------

"Compassion=2C" wrote historian Karen Armstrong in considering the proper=
 meaning of the Golden Rule (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/01/08/kare=
n-armstrong-compassion/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C "asks=
 us to look into our own hearts=2C discover what gives us pain=2C and then=
 refuse=2C under any circumstance whatsoever=2C to inflict that pain on an=
ybody else." In her beautiful ode to compassion (https://www.brainpickings=
=2Eorg/2014/11/04/lucinda-williams-compassion/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D=
[UNIQID]) =2C Lucinda Williams urged: "Have compassion for everyone you m=
eet =E2=80=A6 You do not know what wars are going on down there=2C where t=
he spirit meets the bone."

And yet even the most compassionate among us have one sizable blind spot:=
 the self. Our culture's epidemic of self-criticism (https://www.brainpick=
ings.org/2016/05/23/against-self-criticism-adam-phillips-unforbidden-pleas=
ures/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) has left us woefully unskill=
ed at self-compassion =E2=80=94 that essential anchor of sanity=2C which b=
oth grounds and elevates our spirit.

In this short=2C immensely helpful exercise=2C The School of Life (http://=
www.theschooloflife.com/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) offers a=
 daily self-compassion practice so simple that cynics might mistake it for=
 simplistic =E2=80=94 and yet out of its simplicity arises a profound reor=
ientation to our own selves.

https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/09/05/school-of-life-self-compassion/?m=
c_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

To survive in this high-pressured=2C crazy world=2C most of us have to bec=
ome highly adept at self-criticism. We learn how to tell ourselves off for=
 our failures=2C and for not working hard or smart enough. But so good are=
 we at this that we're sometimes in danger of falling prey to an excessive=
 version of self-criticism =E2=80=94 what we might call self-flagellation:=
 a rather dangerous state=2C which just ushers in depression and underperf=
ormance. We might simply lose the will to get out of bed.

For those moments=2C we need a corrective =E2=80=94 we need to carve out t=
ime for an emotional state of which many of us are profoundly suspicious:=
 self-compassion. We're suspicious because this sounds horribly close to s=
elf-pity. But because depression and self-hatred are serious enemies of a=
 good life=2C we need to appreciate the role of self-care in a good=2C amb=
itious=2C and fruitful life.

Complement with my commencement address on the discipline of resisting cyn=
icism and self-compassion (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/05/16/annenb=
erg-commencement/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) and Ann Patchett=
 on why self-forgiveness is the most important ingredient in making art (h=
ttps://www.brainpickings.org/2015/04/27/ann-patchett-on-writing/?mc_cid=3D=
ddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C then revisit the School of Life's sensi=
tive and sobering animated essays on higher consciousness (https://www.bra=
inpickings.org/2015/11/16/school-of-life-higher-consciousness/?mc_cid=3Ddd=
efbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C what great books do for the soul (https:/=
/www.brainpickings.org/2014/10/09/school-of-life-literature-reading/?mc_ci=
d=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C how to stop letting habit blunt you=
r aliveness (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/06/26/proust-school-of-lif=
e-art/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C what philosophy is for=
 (https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/10/24/what-is-philosophy-for-alain-de=
-botton/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C how to find fulfillin=
g work (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/01/20/school-of-life-fulfilling=
-work/?mc_cid=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C and what comes after re=
ligion
(https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/02/25/school-of-life-religion/?mc_cid=
=3Dddefbb8098&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) .


